-- =============================================================================
-- Section 13: LLPO from Stone Duality
-- =============================================================================

-- The proof of LLPO from Stone Duality (see main-monolithic.tex) goes as follows:
--
-- 1. B_‚ąě is the Boolean algebra generated by (g_n)_{n:‚Ąē} with relations g_m ‚ąß g_n = 0 for m ‚Č† n.
--    Its spectrum ‚Ąē‚ąě = Sp(B_‚ąě) consists of sequences hitting 1 at most once.
--
-- 2. Define f : B_‚ąě ‚Üí B_‚ąě √ó B_‚ąě by:
--    f(g_n) = (g_k, 0) if n = 2k
--    f(g_n) = (0, g_k) if n = 2k+1
--
-- 3. This map is injective (well-defined by the relations).
--
-- 4. By Stone Duality axiom "surjections are formal surjections":
--    f injective ‚üĻ Sp(f) : Sp(B_‚ąě √ó B_‚ąě) ‚Üí Sp(B_‚ąě) is surjective.
--
-- 5. Since Sp(B_‚ąě √ó B_‚ąě) ‚ČÖ ‚Ąē‚ąě + ‚Ąē‚ąě, we get a surjection s : ‚Ąē‚ąě + ‚Ąē‚ąě ‚Üí ‚Ąē‚ąě.
--
-- 6. For any őĪ : ‚Ąē‚ąě, there exists x : ‚Ąē‚ąě + ‚Ąē‚ąě with s(x) = őĪ.
--    - If x = inl(ő≤), then őĪ_{2k+1} = 0 for all k.
--    - If x = inr(ő≤), then őĪ_{2k} = 0 for all k.

-- We postulate LLPO as an axiom that follows from Stone Duality.
-- The full proof requires setting up B_‚ąě quotients which is done in the library.

